## Data flow

- All dashboard data lives in `lib/data/dashboard.ts` ‚Äî types and fixture constants.
- Product-specific data lives in `lib/data/cypher1.ts` and similar files.
- Site-wide constants (`name`, `org`, `tagline`) live in `lib/site.ts`.
- Components receive data as props. No global state management library.
- The only client-side state is `selectedAgent` in the lab dashboard, managed via `useState`.

## Navigation

The site uses a single hamburger-style menu at all breakpoints. The `Nav` component renders a
"Menu" button that toggles a full-width dropdown. There is no separate desktop horizontal link
bar ‚Äî this is intentional, not a bug. Do not add `lg:flex` or `lg:block` alternatives.

## Component conventions

- Named exports only. No `export default`. Every component is `export function ComponentName`.
- Client components (`"use client"`) only when hooks or event handlers are required.
- Page files are server components by default. In Next.js 15, `params` is a Promise.
- Shared components go in `components/`. Dashboard-specific components go in `components/lab/`.
- Components that appear on multiple pages (Nav, Footer, Hero, Section, GlassPanel) are site-wide primitives ‚Äî modify with care.

## Naming

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Types, interfaces, components | PascalCase | `NistCellMapping`, `GlassPanel` |
| Variables, functions | camelCase | `selectedAgent`, `formatTime` |
| Files, directories | PascalCase for components, kebab-case for utils | `Nav.tsx`, `dashboard.ts` |
| CSS classes | kebab-case | `glass-panel`, `glow-number` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `NIST_COLORS`, `DASHBOARD_STATS` |

## Import order

1. React / Next.js imports
2. Component imports (from `@/components/`)
3. Data / utility imports (from `@/lib/`)
4. Type-only imports last
